+    // SwiftGibs: client-side map-vote tally --------------------------------------------------
+    // The server never sends structured vote counts; it only broadcasts (server.cpp)
+    //   "<name> suggests <mode> on map <map> (select map to vote)"
+    // so we reconstruct the tally by parsing that text. Best-effort: a server that rewords the
+    // message just yields no counts (never a crash). Client-only -> stays server-compatible.
+    void changemap(const char *name, int mode); // fwd decl (defined just below)
+
